#: ../../../developers_guide/index.md:5
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/index.md:1
msgid "Developer's Guide"
msgstr "開發者指南"

#: ../../../developers_guide/index.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide is a comprehensive resource for contributing to VTK – for both "
"new and experienced contributors. We welcome your contributions to VTK !"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:2
msgid "Quick Start Guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:4
msgid ""
"This is a quick start guide so that you can start contributing to VTK "
"easily. To understand the process more deeply, you can jump to the [workflow]"
"(./git/develop.md#workflow) section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:8
msgid "Initial Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:10
msgid "Before you begin, perform your initial setup using the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:12
msgid "Register [GitLab Access] to create an account and select a user name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:14
msgid "[Fork VTK][] into your user's namespace on GitLab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:16
msgid ""
"Follow the [download instructions](./git/download.md#clone) to create a "
"local clone of the main VTK repository:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:19
msgid "$ git clone --recursive https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk.git VTK\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:21
msgid "The main repository will be configured as your `origin` remote."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:23
msgid ""
"Run the [developer setup script][] to prepare your VTK work tree and create "
"Git command aliases used below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:26
msgid "$ ./Utilities/SetupForDevelopment.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:28
msgid ""
"This will prompt you for your GitLab username and configure a remote called "
"`gitlab` to refer to your fork. It will also setup a data directory for you. "
"No need to do anything else."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:36
msgid "Development"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:38
msgid "Create a local branch for your changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:40
msgid "git checkout -b your_branch\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:44
msgid ""
"Make the needed changes in VTK and use git locally to create logically "
"separated commits. There is no strict requirements regarding git commit "
"messages syntax but a good rule of thumb to follow is: `General domain: "
"reason for change`, General domain being a class, a module , a specific "
"system like build or CI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:49
msgid ""
"git commit -m \"General domain: Short yet informative reason for the "
"change\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:53
msgid ""
"Build VTK following the [guide][] and fix any build warnings or issues that "
"arise and seems related to your changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:56
msgid ""
"Add/Improve tests in order to ensure your changes are tested. Take a look in "
"the `Testing` directory of the module you are making changes in to see how "
"the tests are currently built and try to follow the same paradigms. Run your "
"test locally from your build directory and check that they pass:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:60
msgid ""
"cmake . && cmake --build .\n"
"ctest -VV -R yourTest\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:65
msgid "Upload"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:67
msgid ""
"Push your changes to the GitLab fork that you created in the [initial setup]"
"(#initial-setup) stage:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:69
msgid "git push gitlab\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:73
msgid "Data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:75
msgid ""
"If your test uses new data or baselines, you will need to add it to your "
"fork. For data, add the file names to the list in your module `yourModule/"
"Testing/CMakeLists.txt` and drop the files in `Testing/Data/`. For "
"baselines, just drop the file in `yourModule/Testing/Data/Baselines` and run "
"the following commands from your build directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:79
msgid "cmake . && cmake --build .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:83
msgid ""
"This will transform your files into .sha512 files. Check your test is "
"passing by running from your build directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:85
msgid "ctest -VV -R yourTest\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:89
msgid "If it passes, add these .sha512 files and commit them, then push with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:91
msgid "git gitlab-push\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:95
msgid "Create a Merge Request"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:97
msgid ""
"Once you are happy with the state of your development on your fork, the next "
"step is to create a merge request back into the main VTK repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:99
msgid ""
"Open [](https://gitlab.kitware.com/username/vtk/-/merge_requests/new) in a "
"browser, select your branch in the list and create a Merge Request against "
"master."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:101
msgid ""
"In the description, write an informative explanation of your added features "
"or bugfix. If there is an associated issue, link it with the `#number` in "
"the description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:103
msgid ""
"Tag some VTK maintainers in the description to ensure someone will see it, "
"see here for the complete [list](./git/develop.md#review-a-merge-request)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:105
msgid "Robot Checks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:107
msgid ""
"Once the MR is created, our GitLab robot will check multiple things and make "
"automated suggestions. Please read them and try to follow the instructions. "
"The two standard suggestions are related to formatting errors and adding "
"markdown changelog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:110
msgid "To fix the formatting, just add a comment containing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:112
msgid "Do: reformat\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:116
msgid ""
"Then, once the robot has fixed the formatting, fetch the changes locally "
"(this will remove any local changes to your branch)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:118
msgid ""
"git fetch gitlab\n"
"git reset --hard gitlab/your_branch\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:123
msgid ""
"To fix the changelog warning, create, add, commit and push a markdown (.md) "
"file in `Documentation/release/dev` folder. In this file, write a small "
"markdown paragraph describing the development. See other .md files in this "
"folder for examples. It may look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:127
msgid ""
"## Development title\n"
"\n"
"A new feature that does this and that has been introduced.\n"
"This specific issue has been fixed in this particular way.\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:134
msgid ""
"Suggestions and best practices on writing the changelog can be found in the "
"`Documentation/release/dev/0-sample-topic.md` file. This is an optional step "
"but recommended to do for any new feature and user facing issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:137
msgid "Reviews"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:139
msgid ""
"VTK maintainers and developers will review your MR by leaving comments on "
"it. Try to follow their instructions and be patient. It can take a while to "
"get a MR into mergeable form. This is a mandatory step, and it is absolutely "
"normal to get change requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:142
msgid ""
"Review comments can be resolved, please resolve a comment once you've taken "
"it into account and pushed related changes or once you've reached an "
"agreement with the commenter that nothing should be changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:145
msgid ""
"Once a reviewer is happy with your changes, they will add a `+X` comment. "
"You need at least one `+2` or higher to consider merging the MR. Two `+1`s "
"do not equal a `+2`. If a reviewer leave a `-1` comment, please discuss with "
"them to understand what is the issue and how it could be fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:148
msgid ""
"Once you have pushed new changes, please tag reviewers again so that they "
"can take a look. If you do not tag reviewers, they may not know to revisit "
"your changes. _Do not hesitate to tag them and ask for help_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:151
msgid "Continuous Integration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:153
msgid ""
"Before merging a MR, the VTK continuous integration (CI) needs to run and be "
"green. For CI to be functional, please read and follow this [guide](https://"
"discourse.vtk.org/t/the-ultimate-how-to-make-ci-work-with-my-fork-"
"guide/7581)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:156
msgid "To run the CI:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:157
msgid "Click on the Pipelines Tab"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:158
msgid "Click on the last pipeline status badge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:159
msgid "Press the `Play all manual` arrows on top of the Build and Test stages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:161
msgid "Do not hesitate to tag a VTK developer for help if needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:163
msgid ""
"You then need to wait for CI to run, it can take a while, up to a full day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:165
msgid ""
"A successful CI should be fully green. If that is so, then your MR is ready !"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:167
msgid ""
"If not, you need to analyse the issues and fix them. Recover the failure "
"information this way:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:169
msgid ""
"Click on the pipelines tab, then on the last status badge, then on the "
"`cdash-commit` job. It will take you to the related CDash report where you "
"will find all information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:172
msgid ""
"Everything in the CDash report should be green except the `NotRun` and "
"`Time` column. Take a look into each issue and fix them locally. If there "
"are issues in the pipeline but nothing is visible in the CDash, please ask a "
"maintainer for help to figure out if anything should be done. You can always "
"try to rerun the failed job by clicking on the arrow of the job in the "
"pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:176
msgid ""
"Once you have fixed some issues locally, commit and push them to gitlab, run "
"the CI again and tag reviewers again for follow-up reviews."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:178
msgid "Merging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:180
msgid ""
"Once the MR has green CI and you have at least one `+2`, you can ask for a "
"merge. Before that please make sure that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:181
msgid ""
"Your commit history is logical (or squashed into a single commit) and "
"cleaned up with good commit messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:182
msgid "You are rebased on a fairly recent version of master"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:184
msgid ""
"If that is not the case, please rebase on master using the following "
"commands:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:186
msgid ""
"git fetch origin\n"
"git rebase -i origin/master\n"
"git push gitlab -f\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:192
msgid ""
"The interactive rebase will let you squash commits, reorganize commits and "
"edit commit messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:194
msgid "After the force push, make sure to run CI again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:196
msgid ""
"Once all is done, tag a VTK developer so that they can perform the merge "
"command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/develop_quickstart.md:198
msgid "__Congratulations ! You just contributed to VTK !__"
msgstr ""
